verbose_text: TF was described to bind to GroEL and increase its affinity for proteins to promote their folding.33 The overexpression of TF showed similar effects to the overexpression of the DnaK-DnaJ-GrpE chaperone team in preventing aggregation of Tv2 / TvCAR, which is due to the highly similar function of DnaK and TF in folding nascent polypeptides.31 Determination of Substrate Scope.
